scenario_text: Reduce the number of available vehicles from 2 to 1 to test the feasibility and impact on total cost when vehicle resources are constrained.
Increase the demand at customer locations 4 and 11 by 50% to test the impact on total cost and feasibility when high-demand customers are present.
Increase the demand at all customer locations by 30% to test the impact on total cost and feasibility when overall demand is significantly higher.
code_modification: {"ADD DATA": "demand = {i: int(d * 1.3) for i, d in demand.items()}"}

scenario_text: Reduce the vehicle capacity from 50 to 30 to test the impact on total cost and feasibility when vehicle capacity is significantly constrained.

Introduce a constraint that requires each vehicle to serve at least one high-demand customer (demand  7) to test the impact on route optimization and feasibility when balancing high-demand customer assignments.
code_modification: {"ADD CONSTRAINT": "model += lpSum(x[i][j] for i in customers for j in customers if demand[i] >= 7) >= K, 'MinHighDemandServe'"}

scenario_text: Introduce a constraint that limits the maximum travel distance for each vehicle to 150 units to test the impact on total cost and feasibility when vehicles have restricted range.
code_modification: {"ADD CONSTRAINT": "model += lpSum(distance[i][j] * x[i][j] for i in nodes for j in nodes) <= 150 * K, 'MaxTravelDistance'"}

scenario_text: Introduce a constraint that requires each vehicle to return to the depot after serving every two customers to test the impact on total cost and feasibility when vehicles have frequent return requirements.
code_modification: {"ADD CONSTRAINT": "for k in range(K): model += lpSum(x[depot][j] for j in customers if j % 2 == k) >= 1, f'ReturnToDepot_Vehicle_{k}'"}

scenario_text: Introduce a constraint that requires each vehicle to serve at least three different customer locations before returning to the depot to test the impact on total cost and feasibility when vehicles have extended service requirements.
code_modification: {"ADD CONSTRAINT": "for k in range(K): model += lpSum(x[i][j] for i in customers for j in customers if i != j) >= 3, f'MinServe_Vehicle_{k}'"}

scenario_text: Introduce a constraint that requires each vehicle to serve a minimum of four customer locations with a combined demand of at least 20 units before returning to the depot to test the impact on total cost and feasibility when vehicles have both extended service and demand requirements.
code_modification: {"ADD CONSTRAINT": "model += lpSum(demand[i] * lpSum(x[i][j] for j in customers) for i in customers) >= 20, 'MinDemandPerVehicle'"}

scenario_text: Introduce a constraint that requires each vehicle to serve at least one customer located more than 70 distance units away from the depot to test the impact on total cost and feasibility when vehicles are required to cover long-distance routes.
code_modification: {"ADD CONSTRAINT": "model += lpSum(x[depot][j] for j in customers if distance[depot][j] > 70) >= K, 'MinLongDistanceServed'"}
